ReportText: Exam: CHEST AP or PA ONLY INDICATION: S/P support device placement. COMPARISON: None. TECHNIQUE: AP supine view of the chest is obtained. FINDINGS: ET tube tip is 2 cm above the carina. NG tube traverses the esophagus and GE junction and is looped in the gastric fundus with distal tip reaching the proximal stomach. Heart size within normal limits. Lung parenchyma and pleural spaces are negative for acute process. No pneumothorax or acute complication. IMPRESSION: No acute process. ET tube tip is 2 cm above the carina.
